    "body": "Moves `stdpath(\"log\")` to `stdpath(\"state\")/logs`, instead of being equivalent to `stdpath(\"state\")`.\r\n\r\nImplements `:log`, a command for easily opening log files in `stdpath(\"log\")`:\r\n- Provides a convenient way to view logs (automatic `G`, tab completion).\r\n- [Missing `:LspLog`](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pull/4234#issuecomment-3661989287) command from nvim-lspconfig becomes `:log lsp`.\r\n\r\ntodo before review: polish, docs\n\nOpen questions during review:\n- Should this command be named `:log` or something else?\n- Should `:log` by itself open the `stdpath(\"log\")` directory, or should it be an alias for `:log nvim`?\r\n\r\nCloses #35082",
    "closed_at": null,
