            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think iter is not available in core: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/ae2829ee35c1fb8649f9d4046c5af48987193d03/src/nvim/CMakeLists.txt#L642-L652",
            "commit_id": "4559474347008263a94ecc1ac3daf153e9dc1a62",
            "created_at": "2026-03-26T20:15:35Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -186,4 +187,38 @@ function M.lsp_complete(line)\n   end\n end\n \n+--- @type string\n+--- @diagnostic disable-next-line: assign-type-mismatch\n+local log_dir = vim.fn.stdpath('log')\n+\n+--- Implements command: `:editlog {file}`.\n+--- @param filename string\n+M.ex_editlog = function(filename)\n+  if filename == '' then\n+    vim.cmd.edit { log_dir }\n+  else\n+    local path = fs.joinpath(log_dir, filename .. '.log')\n+    if not vim.uv.fs_stat(path) then\n+      echo_err((\"No such log file: '%s'\"):format(path))\n+      return\n+    end\n+    vim.cmd.edit { path }\n+    vim.cmd.normal { 'G', bang = true }\n+  end\n+end\n+\n+--- Completion logic for `:editlog` command\n+--- @return string[] list of completions\n+function M.editlog_complete()\n+  return vim\n+    .iter(fs.dir(log_dir))",
